### Description

With a zone-based change detection, this loops change detection indefinitely:

```ts
@Component({
  selector: 'app-child',
  template: `<p>Numbers: {{ numbers() }}</p>`,
})
export class Child {
  numbers = input.required<number[]>();

  constructor() {
    effect(() => {
      console.log(this.numbers());
      // Async tick
      setTimeout(() => {});
    });
  }
}

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  imports: [Child],
  template: `<app-child [numbers]="numbersBiggerThan2" />`,
})
export class App {
  private numbers = [0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5];

  // New array reference on every read
  get numbersBiggerThan2(): number[] {
    return this.numbers.filter((n) => n > 2);
  }
}
```

Such a bug is quite hard to debug, in bigger apps it can cause a browser tab to hang. It'd be great if this could be detected during the compilation or on a dev server. NG0103 error seems related.

